<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d727fn1">The correspondence following was exchanged since
                                the date of the President’s message of December 11,
                            1894.</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Legation of the United States</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-12-10"><hi rend="italic">December 10, 1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Complications arose after your refusal that made the Porte decline your
                            friendly mediation on terms proposed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>